Here is a simple JavaScript program that uses a `for` loop to generate ASCII characters (and their corresponding hexadecimal values) for every number from 0 to 7F. This script assumes the console log of your browser or Node.js terminal to print out the results.

```javascript
let asciiChar = '';
for(let i=0; i<=127; i++){
    // Conversion to ASCII character
    let charCode = i;
    asciiChar = String.fromCharCode(charCode);

    // Conversion to hexadecimal code
    let hexCode = charCode.toString(16);

    console.log('ASCII: ', asciiChar, ' | Hexadecimal: ', hexCode);
}
```

This program uses the `String.fromCharCode()` method to convert a numeric value into an ASCII character and then prints it out along with its corresponding hexadecimal code. The `toString(16)` function is used to get the hexadecimal representation of the numeric ASCII values.

Please note that while the range 0-7F will cover most ASCII characters, this does not include all possible ASCII values, which go up to 255. If you want to print out ASCII characters for every number from 0 to 255, just change `i<=127` to `i<=255`.
